{"id":441,"date":"2020-07-25T09:24:05","date_gmt":"2020-07-25T09:24:05","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/?p=441"},"modified":"2020-07-25T09:24:06","modified_gmt":"2020-07-25T09:24:06","slug":"5-famous-temples-to-visit-in-north-goa","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/5-famous-temples-to-visit-in-north-goa\/","title":{"rendered":"5 Famous temples to visit in North Goa"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Other than the famous beaches, Goa offers various other tourists attractions that add to the reason for visiting this state for vacations. Goa has a rich culture of heritage, history and religion.<br>Today let us check out some Hindu temples in North Goa that you can visit on your next Goa trip.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Mahalaxmi Temple<br><\/strong>Located on the crowded Dr. Dada.Vaidya Road in Panjim, the capital city of Goa, is Shree Mahalaxmi temple. Devoted to Goddess Mahalaxmi, this temple was the first Hindu temple built in 1818 after permission granted by the liberal Portuguese governor Conde De Rio Pardoe.<br>The deity presided in the temple is the goddess of wealth, Shree Mahalaxmi depicted by an image of black stone with four hands. One cannot miss this temple and take the blessings of the goddess while on their Goa vacations.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Shri Saptakoteshwar Temple<br><\/strong>Located in the Narve village of Bicholim city, North Goa, Shri Saptakoteshwar temple is an ancient temple built under the architectural influence of Mughal era. Shree Saptakoteshwar, the deity of the Kadamba dynasty, is an incarnation of Lord Shiva.<br>Janmashtami or locally called as Gokulashtami is most important festival celebrated at this temple in Bicholim and is attended by thousands of devotees.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Shree Lairai Temple<br><\/strong>Famous in Goa for the Shirgao Jatra, Shree Lairai Temple is in village Shrigao in Bicholim. The temple is dedicated to Lairai Devi and displays a combination of the northern and southern styles of temple architecture.<br>The Shirgao Jatra is held in early May and thousands of devotees attend this annual feast of deity to witness the famous rituals of walking of &#8216;dhond&#8217; through sacred fire called Homakund.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Shree Mangeshi temple<br><\/strong>Situated in Priol in the Ponda Taluka, The temple houses the deity Lord Mangueshi. Lord Mangueshi is one of the incarnations of Lord Shiva, The supreme god.<br>The temple is constructed with Goan style of architecture and is a sight to see. The temple also has a 7 storey octagonal lamp tower, painted white with golden arches.<br>During the Magha Purnima, the main annual festival of the temple is held towards the end of February every year. Thousands and thousands of devotees visit this temple to seek the blessings of Lord Mangesh<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Shri Kamakshi Temple<br><\/strong>The Kamakshi temple is dedicated to Goddess Kamakshi. Originally the temple was in Raia in Salcete Taluka but then later, the diety was carried to Shiroda and a temple was built that stand till the present day. <br>Temple design is quite marvellous and resembles a Buddhist pagoda. During the Amavasya, devotees from all over visit the temple to seek the blessing of Shri Kamakshi. Within the vicinity, there are shrines dedicated to Lord Rayeshwara, Lord Hanuman and Dattatreya.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Other than the famous beaches, Goa offers various other tourists attractions that add to the reason for visiting this state for vacations. Goa has a rich culture of heritage, history and religion.Today let us check out some Hindu temples in North Goa that you can visit on your next Goa trip. Mahalaxmi TempleLocated on the [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":442,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http: